{
  "_doc": "Labeled offline detection-quality corpus for the DETERMINISTIC layer (scan_indicators + assemble). Each entry pins the sorted rule-set that fires (golden drift guard) and whether the run signals under a NEUTRAL benign verdict (so `signal` is evidence-driven, per MF3). kind: malicious (must signal) | benign (must NOT signal — FPR floor) | known-fp (signals today; a TRACKED false positive, counted not asserted-clean). Regenerate expected_rules only by consciously re-running the detectors; a silent diff means a regex changed behavior.",
